704164f-a.title: Brooklyn: Farragut Road - Kenilworth Place
704164f-a.text:
2602-2628 Farragut Road, south side, from, but not including Kenilworth Place, to Flatbush Ave. Iu the foreground, is Flatbush Ave.
August 12, 1929.

702678f-c.title: Brooklyn: 26th Street (East) - Farragut Road
702678f-c.text:
(1)
600-608 East 26th Street, at the S.W. corner of Farragut Road,
showing at the corner, the Peter De Baun house, from 1860-1873. This ]  house is not on its original site. In 1906 it was remodeled. The
cupola and wings were removed, and the balcony added, cutting the columns ]  in two.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The sames a more extensive view, showing Amersfort Place in the foregroond]
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing also partially, No. 612 East 26th Street.
June 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

702679f-a.title: Brooklyn: 26th Street (East) - Farragut Road
702679f-a.text:
East 26th Street, east side, between Fareagut Road (left) and Ave. H (right). This street,when laid out will extend north and south, across center of view. A Dutch roofed house is plainly discernible at the left. It faces on Amersfort Place and is known as No. 60. The homes to the right of the last mentioned,face on Nenilworth Place. The Dutch house
has been known as both the Van Nuyse and Ditmars house.
About 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
